config NEPTUNE_STREAM
	tristate "Neptune SDR PL DMA stream"
	depends on OF && HAS_DMA && DMA_ENGINE
	depends on ARCH_ZYNQ || COMPILE_TEST
	help
	  Own a DMA-coherent PL-to-PS receive ring for the Neptune SDR edge
	  data path using a DT-provided DMAEngine channel.  A single consumer
	  uses poll, fixed-width ioctls, and a read-only mmap to acquire and
	  release generation-tagged slots.  A separate nonexclusive read-only
	  status node exposes canonical PL health without mapping MMIO.

	  This driver does not use Linux IIO userspace reads for payloads.  It
	  binds only to a matching v1 PL register contract and fails probe for
	  unknown hardware, unsupported DMA mmap, or incomplete DT resources.

	  The source is deliberately limited to Linux 5.10 through 6.12.  The
	  repository's pinned Linux 4.14 development image is not supported.
